{"word":"G2588 - καρδία - kardía - kar-dee'-ah - Heart","slug":"G2588","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">καρδία</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kardía"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kar-dee'-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Heart"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03C1;&#x03B4;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B1; - kardia</b> - <i>kar-dee'-ah</i><p/>Prolonged from a primary <b>&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03C1;</b> <b>kar</b> (Latin <i>cor</i>, &ldquo;heart&rdquo;); the <i>heart</i>, that is, (figuratively) the <i>thoughts</i> or <i>feelings</i> (<i>mind</i>); also (by analogy) the <i>middle:</i> - (+ broken-) heart (-ed)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2589\">G2589</a>, <a href=\"#/G4641\">G4641</a>"}]}